g.text: This is a concept map of Machine Learning. If you think of any missing concept, please submit a PR @ https://github.com/tomzx/machine-learning-concept-map.
Use the scrollbars or your middle mouse click to navigate. You can click on nodes, which will bring you to an associated website.
Page found on Wikipedia, but not manually validated
A concept is complete if it covers all positive examples.
A concept is consistent if it covers none of the negative examples.
The version space is the set of all complete and consistent concepts. This set is convex and is fully defined by its least and most general elements.
